n lo=\r\nve a whole universe unconditionally, are possibly the closest to this\n&gt; sup=\r\nreme and unknowable force. In common language, we call them Rishis.\n&gt;\n&gt; I l=\r\nike all forms of Deities, for I find something beautiful in everyone of\n&gt; t=\r\nhem. And I also like the One behind forms, which is so perfectly\n&gt; transcen=\r\ndental that it cannot be comprehended ever. It&#39;s like the surface\n&gt; area of=\r\n the fine tip of a needle, or the gap between the two breaths, or\n&gt; the mil=\r\nlionth part of a single hair, or the endless-ness of space, or the\n&gt; bottom=\r\nless well of stillness in the mind at certain points in meditation.\n&gt; The o=\r\nnly thing that stops me from getting a better understanding the\n&gt; grandeur =\r\nof  this formless entity are the limitations of my own mind and\n&gt; body, tha=\r\nt I have acquired over millions of births. That is why Sadhana. To\n&gt; slowly=\r\n gnaw away at my own mind, to be better able to appreciate this\n&gt; endless, =\r\nnameless entity. G_d.\n&gt;\n&gt;\n&gt; I do not believe in Moksha. What is Moksha? No =\r\nrebirth? If the Universe\n&gt; itself gets born over and over and over, if Rama=\r\n and Krshna come back at\n&gt; every cycle, who am I to demand that I should no=\r\nt get born? Infact, when a\n&gt; person proverbially finishes off his/her karma=\r\ns, they merely go to another\n&gt; plane in this Universe and stay there for eo=\r\nns of time, since time anyway\n&gt; moves very, very slowly in different realms=\r\n. But then, if this force so\n&gt; wants, it can send back any of the souls fro=\r\nm any of the realms to any of\n&gt; the other realms to serve a certain functio=\r\nn. And if a soul stays in a\n&gt; certain higher realm and in forced to take re=\r\nbirth again, the seeds of the\n&gt; karmas - which never really die off - are  =\r\nwatered again by the environment\n&gt; of birth and they sprout into saplings. =\r\nAnd this may go even beyond one\n&gt; cycle