external obj=\r\nective reality is Shakti. Extending this principle to the Universe, the pur=\r\nely transcendental non-changing, non-negotiable reality can be called the &=\r\nquot;atmah&quot; while everything else, semi-transcendental to the objectiv=\r\ne\n reality all around is Shakti. Thus in short, using scriptural terms, Nir=\r\nguna Brahman is the state of mind of God, while the Universe(s)/various rea=\r\nlm(s) is the body of God. Both are irrevocable linked for all practical pur=\r\nposes.=A0 Maya is whatever inhibits an individual cell (a human being or an=\r\nimal or plant or anything) in the body of the God - that is Universe(s) - f=\r\nrom realizing the greater picture. &lt;br&gt;\n\n&lt;br&gt;Am I making sense? -:)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;=\r\n-Regards&lt;br&gt;=A0Rajarshi&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=3D&quot;im&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;div =\r\nclass=3D&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-family:times new roman,new york,tim=\r\nes,serif&quot;&gt;awaktam wyaktimApannam manyantE mAmabuddhayah |&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n\n&lt;b&gt;&lt;s=\r\npan style=3D&quot;FONT-SIZE:10pt;COLOR:navy;FONT-FAMILY:Verdana&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;=\r\n#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt; param bhAwamajAnanto mamAwyaya=\r\nmanuttamam\n ||[7:24]&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;=\r\n&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;font-family:verdana,helvetica,sans-serif;fo=\r\nnt-size:10pt&quot;&gt; &lt;div style=3D&quot;font-family:times new roman,new york,times,ser=\r\nif;font-size:12pt&quot;&gt;\n\n &lt;div dir=3D&quot;ltr&quot;&gt; &lt;font face=3D&quot;Arial&quot;&gt; &lt;hr size=3D&quot;1=\r\n&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=3D&quot;im&quot;&gt;  &lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-weight:bold&quot;&gt;From:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt; =\r\nAjit Krishnan &lt;&lt;a href=3D&quot;mailto:ajit.krishn